Kwara United reclaimed top spot in the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) after a demolition of Adamawa United in Ilorin yesterday. Stephen Jude bagged a hat-trick and a brace by Michael Ohanu secured a memorable win for the home team. Kwara United now top the standings with 30 points from 17 points. Kano Pillars moved to second position on the table following a 2-1 away win against Wikki Tourists. At the Agege Stadium, Akwa United also beat their hosts MFM 2-1. Mfon Udoh puts Akwa United in front courtesy of an assist from Ikechukwu Nwani two minutes from break. While in Makurdi, Lobi Stars thrashed Rivers United 4-1.